parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brakes do not function properly
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle skids or hydroplanes
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke comes from the hood of the vehicle
and the wiring for the ABS catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not work
and the fuel pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The frame is rusted
corroded
or broken
causing the vehicle to sway or lose control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear suspension lower link brackets are broken or detached
causing the vehicle to sway or lose control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes are faulty
causing the vehicle to slide or lose control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall repair may not be adequate, leaving the vehicle unsafe to drive.
symptoms: The recall repair did not fix the underlying issue
and the vehicle is still unsafe to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in unexpected fuel exhaustion, stalling, or accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge reads incorrectly
shows empty when there is still fuel in the tank
fuel light blinks or stays on
gauge needle drops to empty after filling up
and erratic fuel level readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the actual fuel level, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, stalling, or accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge does not work
shows incorrect readings
fuel light blinks or stays on
and erratic fuel level readings.
